#### <span id="iv.iv.vi.ii-p0.1"></span>Chapter II.

<span id="iv.iv.vi.ii-p1"></span>Abbot Serapion’s enumeration of eight
principal faults.

<span id="iv.iv.vi.ii-p2"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="iv.iv.vi.ii-p2.1"></span>There</span> are eight principal faults
which attack mankind; viz., first gastrimargia, which means gluttony,
secondly fornication, thirdly philargyria, i.e., avarice or the love of
money, fourthly anger, fifthly dejection, sixthly acedia, i.e.,
listlessness or low spirits, seventhly cenodoxia, i.e., boasting or vain
glory; and eighthly pride.

